# BaseCard API Test File
# Use with VS Code REST Client extension or similar tools

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@address = 0x1234567890123456789012345678901234567890

### Get all cards
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/cards

### Get card by address
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/cards?address={{address}}

### Get card by address (alternative endpoint)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/card/{{address}}

### Create a new card
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cards
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nickname": "Test User",
  "bio": "This is a test user bio",
  "imageURI": "https://example.com/image.jpg",
  "basename": "testuser",
  "role": "Developer",
  "skills": ["JavaScript", "TypeScript", "React"],
  "address": "0xabcdef1234567890123456789012345678901234"
}

### Update a card
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/card/{{address}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nickname": "Updated Lucky Jerry",
  "bio": "Updated bio for Jerry",
  "role": "Senior Developer",
  "skills": ["JavaScript", "TypeScript", "React", "Node.js"]
}

### Get collections for a card
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/collections?id=1

### Add a card to collection
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/collections
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cardId": 1,
  "collectCardId": 2
}

### Get all programs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/programs

### Create a new program
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/programs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "New Bounty Program",
  "description": "# New Bounty Program\n\nThis is a **markdown** description for the bounty program.\n\n## Requirements\n- Skill 1\n- Skill 2\n- Skill 3",
  "ownerCardId": 1,
  "type": "bounty"
}

### Create a new project
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/programs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "New Project",
  "description": "# New Project\n\nThis is a project description with markdown support.",
  "ownerCardId": 1,
  "type": "project"
}
